Your Honor,

I stand before you today, pleading guilty to the charges of careless driving. It is with great remorse that I acknowledge my actions on that fateful day. I was rushing to the airport to pick up my family members, feeling the weight of the time ticking away. In my haste, I chose to drive aggressively and exceed the speed limit, putting not only my own safety, but also the safety of others at risk.

I must also admit that I made a grave mistake by answering a text message from my cousin while driving. This momentary lapse in judgment caused me to lose focus, resulting in a collision with a guardrail. I am grateful that no one else was harmed in this incident, but I am acutely aware of the potential consequences my reckless behavior could have had.

In reflecting on this incident, I have come to the realization of just how dangerous my actions were and the potential for harm they carried. I am deeply remorseful for the recklessness that I displayed on that day. However, I would like to take this opportunity to express my gratitude that no one else was affected by my poor decision-making.

At 37 years old, I have maintained a clean record up to this point, with the exception of the three penalty points I already have for speeding. I understand the gravity of my actions and I am fully committed to learning from this experience. I recognize the importance of road safety and the need to prioritize the well-being of myself and those around me.

In addition to my commitment to personal growth, I would like to highlight my regular donations to the British Heart Foundation. Through my contributions, I have aimed to make a positive impact on the lives of others. While not directly related to the offense at hand, I believe it demonstrates my character and my desire to contribute to society in a meaningful way.

Your Honor, I stand before you today with a heavy heart, fully accepting responsibility for my actions. I am pleading guilty to the charge of careless driving and I sincerely apologize for the harm that I have caused. I assure you that I have learned a valuable lesson from this experience and I am dedicated to making amends and preventing such a situation from occurring again in the future.

Thank you for your attention, Your Honor.

